data.name: Venus Climate Orbiter Akatsuki IR2 Longitude-Latitude Map Data
data.description: This dataset contains longitude-latitude map data created from images acquired by the IR2 instrument of the Venus Climate Orbiter (VCO, also known as PLANET-C and AKATSUKI) spacecraft. This dataset consists of NetCDF and FITS files. The longitude-latitude map data are included as Level 3 product in NetCDF. During process of creating longitude-latitude map data, pointing of spacecraft was corrected using limb-fitting technique. Detected limb points and information on fitted ellipse are provided as auxiliary data, Level 3x product in NetCDF. Level 3x product in FITS is also provided, which can be used as geometry information file with poiting correction instead of 'geo' file provided in VCO-V-IR2-3-SEDR-V1.0. This dataset is produced from calibrated image, geometry information, and SPICE kernel datasets. Please refer VCO-V-IR2-3-CDR-V1.0, VCO-V-IR2-3-SEDR-V1.0, and VCO-V-SPICE-6-V1.0 datasets for detailed information on the instrument and acquired data.

data.name: MAXI/GSC All-sky X-ray maps
data.description: MAXI (Monitor of All-sky X-ray Image) is mounted on the Japanese Experimental Module (KIBO) of the International Space Station. MAXI has been developed in collaboration of JAXA and RIKEN. MAXI has not only a wide field of view, but also a higher sensitivity than previous all-sky monitors by an order of magnitude. The observation has started in August 2009. More detailed information on MAXI can be found in the MAXI homepage at RIKEN, which produces and archives high-level data products such as images and light-curves for public release. MAXI carries two types of instruments, Gas Slit Camera (GSC) and Solid-state Slit Camera (SSC). The GSC is composed of 12 one-dimensional PSPCs (counter ID = 0-9, A, B), and covers the 2 -- 30 keV energy range with an energy resolution of 18 % (5.9 keV). The SSC is composed of two cameras, SSC-H and SSC-Z, each has 16 chips of X-ray CCDs, and covers the 0.5 -- 12 keV energy range with an energy resolution of < 150 eV (5.9 keV).

data.name: MAXI All sky X-ray Monitor data for standard analysis
data.description: MAXI (Monitor of All-sky X-ray Image) is mounted on the Japanese Experimental Module (KIBO) of the International Space Station. MAXI has been developed in collaboration of JAXA and RIKEN. MAXI has not only a wide field of view, but also a higher sensitivity than previous all-sky monitors by an order of magnitude. The observation has started in August 2009. More detailed information on MAXI can be found in the MAXI homepage at RIKEN, which produces and archives high-level data products such as images and light-curves for public release. MAXI carries two types of instruments, Gas Slit Camera (GSC) and Solid-state Slit Camera (SSC). The GSC is composed of 12 one-dimensional PSPCs (counter ID = 0-9, A, B), and covers the 2 -- 30 keV energy range with an energy resolution of 18 % (5.9 keV). The SSC is composed of two cameras, SSC-H and SSC-Z, each has 16 chips of X-ray CCDs, and covers the 0.5 -- 12 keV energy range with an energy resolution of < 150 eV (5.9 keV).

data.name: MAXI/RBM timeseries data
data.description: MAXI (Monitor of All-sky X-ray Image) is mounted on the Japanese Experimental Module (KIBO) of the International Space Station. MAXI has been developed in collaboration of JAXA and RIKEN. MAXI has not only a wide field of view, but also a higher sensitivity than previous all-sky monitors by an order of magnitude. The observation has started in August 2009. More detailed information on MAXI can be found in the MAXI homepage at RIKEN, which produces and archives high-level data products such as images and light-curves for public release. MAXI carries two types of instruments, Gas Slit Camera (GSC) and Solid-state Slit Camera (SSC). The GSC is composed of 12 one-dimensional PSPCs (counter ID = 0-9, A, B), and covers the 2 -- 30 keV energy range with an energy resolution of 18 % (5.9 keV). The SSC is composed of two cameras, SSC-H and SSC-Z, each has 16 chips of X-ray CCDs, and covers the 0.5 -- 12 keV energy range with an energy resolution of < 150 eV (5.9 keV).

dataset.name: MAXI/GSC All-sky X-ray maps
dataset.description: MAXI (Monitor of All-sky X-ray Image) is mounted on the Japanese Experimental Module (KIBO) of the International Space Station. MAXI has been developed in collaboration of JAXA and RIKEN. MAXI has not only a wide field of view, but also a higher sensitivity than previous all-sky monitors by an order of magnitude. The observation has started in August 2009. More detailed information on MAXI can be found in the MAXI homepage at RIKEN, which produces and archives high-level data products such as images and light-curves for public release. MAXI carries two types of instruments, Gas Slit Camera (GSC) and Solid-state Slit Camera (SSC). The GSC is composed of 12 one-dimensional PSPCs (counter ID = 0-9, A, B), and covers the 2 -- 30 keV energy range with an energy resolution of 18 % (5.9 keV). The SSC is composed of two cameras, SSC-H and SSC-Z, each has 16 chips of X-ray CCDs, and covers the 0.5 -- 12 keV energy range with an energy resolution of < 150 eV (5.9 keV).

dataset.name: Venus Climate Orbiter Akatsuki SPICE Kernel PDS3 dataset
dataset.description: This dataset includes the complete set of Venus Climate Orbiter (VCO, also known as PLANET-C and AKATSUKI) SPICE data files, i.e., kernel files, for the cruise, the sun orbiting, and the science phase(s) of the mission. The SPICE data files, which can be accessed using SPICE software, contain geometric and other ancillary information needed to recover the full value of the science instrument data. In particular SPICE kernels provide spacecraft and planetary ephemerides, instrument mounting alignments, spacecraft orientation, spacecraft sequences of events, and data needed for relevant time conversions. This dataset is compliant with the PDS3 Standards, and is superseded by Venus Climate Orbiter Akatsuki SPICE Kernel Archive Bundle which is compliant with the PDS4 Standards.

The UVI EDRs are considered Level 2 or Edited Data (equivalent to NASA Level 1A). The EDRs are reconstructed from Level 1 or Raw Data. This dataset consists entirely of FITS files. dataset.name: Venus Climate Orbiter Akatsuki UVI Longitude-Latitude Map Data
dataset.description: This dataset contains longitude-latitude map data created from images acquired by the UVI instrument of the Venus Climate Orbiter (VCO, also known as PLANET-C and AKATSUKI) spacecraft. This dataset consists of NetCDF and FITS files. The longitude-latitude map data are included as Level 3 product in NetCDF. During process of creating longitude-latitude map data, pointing of spacecraft was corrected using limb-fitting technique. Detected limb points and information on fitted ellipse are provided as auxiliary data, Level 3x product in NetCDF. Level 3x product in FITS is also provided, which can be used as geometry information file with poiting correction instead of 'geo' file provided in VCO-V-UVI-3-SEDR-V1.0. This dataset is produced from calibrated image, geometry information, and SPICE kernel datasets. Please refer VCO-V-UVI-3-CDR-V1.0, VCO-V-UVI-3-SEDR-V1.0, and VCO-V-SPICE-6-V1.0 datasets for detailed information on the instrument and acquired data.
